<subSubSection type="etymology">
<paragraph pageNumber="625">
Etymology Gr 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181990" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole epetrion Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole epetrion Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="625" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="epetrion">epetrion</taxonomicName>
, needle, referring to the needle-like propodeal spine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageNumber="625">
diagnosis A member of the 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33994" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole scrobifera Emery" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole scrobifera Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="625" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scrobifera">scrobifera</taxonomicName>
group known only from the minor, close to 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181989" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole arctos Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole arctos Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="625" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arctos">arctos</taxonomicName>
of northeastern Mexico and 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181995" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole thrasys Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole thrasys Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="625" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thrasys">thrasys</taxonomicName>
of Panama, differing in the longer propodeal spines, carinulate genae, absence of a nuchal collar, and mostly foveolate, opaque dorsal half of the head capsule.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
